label.value: Cell Separation by Density Gradient Centrifugation

value.value: A method of separating cells by either their differential rate of sedimentation in a centrifugal gradient or their differential buoyancy in a density gradient.
The collection of the fluid portion of non-human blood intended as a source material for further manufacture.

label.value: Harvest of Product from Cell Media

value.value: Collection of a material of interest from a cell culture supernatant.

label.value: Harvest of Product from Whole Cell Lysate

value.value: Collection of a material of interest from a cell lysate.

label.value: Human Blood Product-Derived Intermediate Paste Production

value.value: The production of concentrated proteins from human plasma during a protein purification process.
A multistep purification process that isolates plasma proteins based upon the differential solubility of proteins in ethanol solutions.
A process to isolate plasma proteins by cooling the plasma to form a precipitate.

label.value: Preparation of Blood Products Grouping Reagent

value.value: A procedure to isolate blood group antigens for use in serological testing.

label.value: Production of Blood Serological Test Device

value.value: A procedure to manufacture devices or components used in blood serological testing.
A process that isolates a material of interest from a cell culture using a biomolecular separation technique.

label.value: Sample Recovery from Cell Culture, Not Otherwise Specified

value.value: A cell culture sample collection process that is not otherwise specified.

label.value: Sedimentation Sample Separation from Cell Culture

value.value: A process that collects a material of interest from a cell culture sample by allowing the materials harvested from the culture to separate by sedimentation.
Cell culture techniques done under aseptic conditions.
The physical, chemical and/or enzymatic processing of tissue samples to remove cells and leave behind the extracellular matrix or natural scaffold made up of collagen and other fibers and proteins.

label.value: Recovery of Plasma from Blood Products

value.value: A process that derives plasma from single units of whole blood or as a by-product from the preparation of blood components from whole blood.
Indicates that a product is derived from a specified mineral material.

A process that takes a single pool of cells prepared from a selected cell clone and determines the characteristics of a sample of the cells including, but not limited to, checking for microbial or viral contaminants, the optimal growth conditions, and levels of expression of biologics.

A process that generates and maintains a single pool of cells prepared from a selected cell clone under specific conditions. This involves dispensing the cell sample into multiple containers and storing the sample under specific conditions.
The expansion of a cell line in multiple vessels followed by the harvesting and pooling of the expanded culture into one vessel for holding or storage.
A type of culture in which cells are grown in single use bags.
A type of culture in which cells are grown in flasks or bottles.
A type of culture in which cells are grown and are continuously fed new culture media.
Addition of living cells to a biocompatible scaffold.
A layer of supportive cells that are irradiated to prevent replication but can still secrete growth enhancing factors for use in co-culture
A process that synthesizes a material of interest using a large scale cell culture that is grown in a bioreactor.

label.value: Cell Culture-Based Biosynthesis, Not Otherwise Specified

value.value: A process that synthesizes a material of interest using cell culture that is not otherwise specified.
A process that synthesizes a material of interest using a disposable bag cell culture.
A process that synthesizes a material of interest using a continuously fed cell culture.

label.value: Shaker Flask or Roller Bottle Culture Biosynthesis

value.value: A process that synthesizes a material of interest using shaker flask or roller bottle cell culture.
Preservation of cells or genetic vectors by storage at low temperatures.

label.value: Design and Specification of Software Platform or Architecture for in Vitro Diagnostics Device

value.value: The act of specifying the operational and physical requirements, respectively, for the software and hardware of an in vitro diagnostic device.
The shipment of blood products under controlled conditions.
A method that coats a cellular product with a layer of another material.

label.value: Coating of Device with Immunologic Reagents

value.value: A procedure used to immobilize antigens or immunoglobulins on a device.
A process that forms a solid dosage unit by applying mechanical forces to bind the formulation.
A process that forms a solid dosage unit by continuously cutting a uniform material into equally sized segments.

label.value: Drug Formulation Process, Not Otherwise Specified

value.value: A process that forms a dosage that is not otherwise specified.
A method that suspends a substrate in a fluidized bed while it is sprayed with a layer of coating material.
A process that forms a solid dosage unit consisting of discrete layers that are bound together.
A process that uses a laser to drill holes in a tablet.
A process that forms a solid dosage unit by pouring or casting a melted agent into a prefabricated form.
A method that rolls a substrate such that it comes into contact with the coating material.
A method that agitates a substrate in a rotating pan while it is sprayed with a layer of coating material.
A method that condenses a vaporized coating material onto a substrate.
A process that is not otherwise specified, which removes water or a volatile solvent by evaporation.
A process that removes water or volatile solvents from a bed of solids by relying on absorption of heat radiation by those solvents.
